title: 10 Things To Know: Ohio State VS. Maryland
text:
By 10TV Web Staff Thursday October 8, 2015 8:44 PM UPDATED: Friday October 9, 2015 11:41 AM COLUMBUS, Ohio - 
The Maryland Terrapins come to town this weekend to face undefeated Ohio State in their home conference opener. 
The Terrapins come in sporting a 2-3 record, kick off will be at Noon inside Ohio Stadium. 
Here are 10 things to know before the game: 
1. Round 2 
This is only the second time Ohio State has played Maryland, Ohio State won the inaugural matchup 52-24 last season. 

2. Zeke The Freak! 
RB Ezekiel Elliott is coming off a performance in which he was named Big Ten offensive player of the week, where he rushed for three touchdowns and a career-high 274 yards. 

3. Sitting Atop The Leaderboards 
Ohio State now joins Oklahoma atop the list for most appearances as the No. 1-Ranked team in the country according to the Associated Press Poll with 101 total appearances. 

4. Go-To Guy Through The Air 
WR Michael Thomas is entering the game with a streak of 21 straight games with a reception while leading the team this year with 20 receptions for 292 yards and 4 touchdowns. 

5. The Best This League Has To Offer 
Cameron Johnston leads the Big Ten in punting averaging 46.3yds per kick, while Linebacker Raekwon McMillan leads the Big Ten in Tackles per game with 10.8. 

6. Heisman Worthy Half 
Ezekiel Elliott rushed for 243 yards alone in the second half of the Indiana game, the most in Ohio State history for a single half. All three of his rushing touchdowns in the second half were for more than 50 yards. 

7. Silver Bullet Defense 
Ohio State’s defense this season has only allowed 10 plays for 20 or more yards while only one of those has come from a running play. 

8. Marshall And Washington Set Career Marks 
Jalen Marshall is coming off a career came in which he had six catches for 110 yards of receiving and six punt returns for 76 yards with a long of 38. Adolphus Washington also set a career high with ten tackles. 

9. Can We Talk A Little More About Zeke? 
Ezekiel Elliott is currently leading the Big Ten in three major statistical categories. He is first in the league with 145.8 rushing yds/gm, 161 all-purpose yds/gm and lastly he is tied for the league lead in scoring with 9.6 ppg. 

10. How Many Streaks Can One Team Have? 
The Buckeyes continued to ride the nation’s longest win streak to 18 with their victory over Indiana. Starting QB, Cardale Jones, was able to improve his record to a perfect 8-0 with the win as well. ©2015 by 10TV.com. All rights reserved.
